Royal Media Services CEO Wachira Waruru has been elected as the new chairperson of the Media Owners Association. Nation Media Group’s Editor-in-Chief Tom Mshindi was elected as the vice-chairperson while the acting Standard Group CEO Orlando Lyomu will serve as the secretary. Media Max CEO Ian Fernandes will hold the position of treasurer while Radio Africa Group chief operating officer Agnes Kalekye will serve as the organising secretary. The new officials were elected during the associations annual general meeting in Nairobi on Friday. Click here for the latest political news   